Bioinformatic Figures with ggplot2

1. barplot

rm(list=ls())

# barplot 
x = c(1,2,3,4,5)
barplot(x)
title(main = "barplot",xlab = "factor",ylab="value")

barplot(x,col = c("red","blue","orange"))

barplot(x,col = c("red","blue","orange"),border = F)
# barplot with ggplot2
library(ggplot2)

library(ggsci)
y = c("a","b","c","d","e")
z = data.frame(x,y)
ggplot(z,aes(y,x))+geom_bar(stat="identity")#

ggplot(z,aes(y,x,fill =y))+geom_bar(stat="identity")#

ggplot(z,aes(y,x,fill =y))+geom_bar(stat="identity")+scale_fill_npg()#NPG

##2. Scatter plot

# scatter plot 
x = c(1:20)
y = c(1:20) ^ 2
plot(x=x,y=y)

plot(x=x,y=y,pch=19,col = "blue",xlab = "test X",ylab = "test Y",main = "Test scatter plot")
abline(a = 0,b = 1)

ggplot(data.frame(x,y),aes(x,y))+geom_point()+geom_smooth()+labs(x="test X",y="test Y")
## `geom_smooth()` using method = 'loess' and formula 'y ~ x'

##4. histogram

x1 = rnorm(100000,10,2)

hist(x1,probability = T,xlim = c(0,20))

lines(density(x1),lwd=3)

hist(x1,probability = T,xlim = c(0,20))
lines(density(x1),lwd=3,lty=3)

hist(x1,probability = T,xlim = c(0,20),col="orange",border = F)
lines(density(x1),lwd=3,lty=3,col="blue")

dat <- data.frame (cond = factor(rep(c("A","B"),each=20000)),rating = rnorm(20000,mean=0.8))
ggplot(dat, aes(x=rating))+geom_density()

ggplot(dat, aes(x=rating))+geom_histogram()
## `stat_bin()` using `bins = 30`. Pick better value with `binwidth`.

ggplot(dat, aes(x=rating))+geom_histogram(aes(y=..density..),colour="black",fill ="white")+geom_density(alpha=0.2,fill="#FF6666")
## `stat_bin()` using `bins = 30`. Pick better value with `binwidth`.

##6. Q-Q plot ###

x1 = log2(rnorm(10000,mean = 10,2))
x2 = rnorm(10000,mean = 15,2)

x1.quantile = quantile(x1,probs = seq(0,1,0.01))
x2.quantile = quantile(x2,probs = seq(0,1,0.01))

plot(x=x1.quantile,y=x2.quantile,xlim=c(0,20),ylim=c(0,20),col = "pink")
abline(a=0,b=1)

qqplot(x1.quantile,x2.quantile)

# 0gene
gene_diff_table.filter = gene_diff_table[gene_diff_table$value_1 > 0 & gene_diff_table$value_2 > 0,]

# MA
M.value = log2(gene_diff_table.filter$value_2 / gene_diff_table.filter$value_1)
A.value = log2(sqrt(gene_diff_table.filter$value_2 * gene_diff_table.filter$value_1) + 1)

# 
plot(x=A.value,y=M.value)

plot(x=A.value,y=M.value,pch=19,cex=0.2)

plot(x=A.value,y=M.value,pch=19,cex=0.2,col="gray")

plot(x=A.value,y=M.value,pch=19,cex=0.2,col=rgb(0,0,1,0.05))

plot(x=A.value,y=M.value,pch=19,cex=0.5,col=rgb(0,0,1,0.05),xlim = c(0,12),ylim=c(-5,5))

# change color 
color.vec = rep("gray",length(M.value))
color.vec[M.value > 1] = "red"
color.vec[M.value < -1] = "blue"

plot(x=A.value,y=M.value,pch=19,cex=0.5,col=color.vec,xlim = c(0,12),ylim=c(-5,5))
abline(h=0,lty=3,lwd=1.5)

# volcano plot 
x.fold_change = log2(gene_diff_table.filter$value_2 / gene_diff_table.filter$value_1)
y.pvalue = -1* log10(gene_diff_table.filter$q_value)

plot(x=x.fold_change,y=y.pvalue)

plot(x=x.fold_change,y=y.pvalue,pch=19,cex=0.5,xlim=c(-4,4))

color.vec = rep("gray",length(x.fold_change))
color.vec[x.fold_change > 1 & y.pvalue > log10(0.05) * -1] = "red"
color.vec[x.fold_change < -1 & y.pvalue > log10(0.05) * -1] = "blue"

plot(x=x.fold_change,y=y.pvalue,pch=19,cex=0.5,xlim=c(-4,4),col=color.vec)

x1 = rnorm(10000,10,1)
x2 = rnorm(10000,12,2)

x1.cdf = ecdf(x1)
x2.cdf = ecdf(x2)

plot(x1.cdf,xlim=c(5,20),col="gray",lwd=3)
lines(x2.cdf,col="blue",lwd=3)

ks.test(x1,x2)
## 
##  Two-sample Kolmogorov-Smirnov test
## 
## data:  x1 and x2
## D = 0.5391, p-value < 2.2e-16
## alternative hypothesis: two-sided
